PhoneNumberSection.Name: CountryCode
PhoneNumberSection.Notes: Country code locates the phone number within a specific country and is a specially formatted number between 1 and 999

PhoneNumberSection.Name: AreaCode
PhoneNumberSection.Notes: Most country phone numbers start with an area code, which locates the phone number within a specific section of the country.

PhoneNumberSection.Name: CentralOfficeCode
PhoneNumberSection.Notes: Most phone numbers include a section after the area code which locates a specific district or region within the area code.

PhoneNumberSection.Name: SubscriberNumber
PhoneNumberSection.Notes: This refers to whatever remaining parts of the number are left that identify the specific subscriber being called.

PhoneNumberSection.Name: ExtraNumbers
PhoneNumberSection.Notes: This refers to any extra numbers after the subscriber number.  In some situations these numbers are just ignored, in other cases, they will make the number unroutable.
